										<content:encoded><![CDATA[
<h1 class="has-text-align-center"><strong>15 E-Commerce Survey Examples You’ll Want to Copy</strong></h1>
<div class="post-content-category"><a href="https://sleeknote.com/blog/category/conversion-rate-optimization" rel="category tag">Conversion Rate Optimization</a></div>


<figure class="wp-block-image alignwide size-large"><img width="1024" height="437" src="https://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/E-Commerce-Survey-Examples-WordPress-1024x437.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-118453" srcset="https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/E-Commerce-Survey-Examples-WordPress-1024x437.jpg 1024w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/E-Commerce-Survey-Examples-WordPress-300x128.jpg 300w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/E-Commerce-Survey-Examples-WordPress-768x328.jpg 768w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/E-Commerce-Survey-Examples-WordPress-1536x656.jpg 1536w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/E-Commerce-Survey-Examples-WordPress-2048x875.jpg 2048w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/E-Commerce-Survey-Examples-WordPress-380x162.jpg 380w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/E-Commerce-Survey-Examples-WordPress-600x256.jpg 600w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/E-Commerce-Survey-Examples-WordPress-760x325.jpg 760w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/E-Commerce-Survey-Examples-WordPress-1440x615.jpg 1440w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/E-Commerce-Survey-Examples-WordPress-960x410.jpg 960w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/E-Commerce-Survey-Examples-WordPress-82x35.jpg 82w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/E-Commerce-Survey-Examples-WordPress-117x50.jpg 117w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/E-Commerce-Survey-Examples-WordPress-740x316.jpg 740w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/E-Commerce-Survey-Examples-WordPress-220x94.jpg 220w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/E-Commerce-Survey-Examples-WordPress-385x164.jpg 385w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /></figure>


<div id="preamble-block_6051f2abd5948" class="block-preamble"><p><span style="font-weight: 400;">You’ve got a great product. When people buy it, you deliver it on time. So surely everyone loves you?</span></p>
</div>






<p>Not necessarily. Product and fulfillment are only two parts in the customer satisfaction puzzle. If you provide a poor experience to customers, it really doesn’t matter if you offer the cheapest or highest-quality product on the market—there’s a good chance you’ll never see them again.</p>



<p>The thing is, shoppers, don’t have a “three-strikes” policy. According to business intelligence firm SAS, one in three customers would ditch a brand after a single <a href="https://www.sas.com/en_gb/news/press-releases/2020/october/a-third-of-customers-would-ditch-companies-after-just-one-poor-experience.html" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">poor experience</a>, while 90 percent would do so after two to five poor experiences. Instead of buying from you, they’ll look elsewhere.&nbsp;</p>



<p>In other words, if you’re delivering a bad customer experience, you’re effectively doing your competitors’ marketing for them.</p>



<p>But while it’s undeniably important, “customer experience” is quite a nebulous term that can mean different things to different people. When respondents to the same SAS survey were asked to rank their biggest customer experience concerns, the results were wide-ranging and evenly spread:</p>



<ol><li>Convenience (cited by 38 percent of respondents)</li><li>Responsive customer support (32 percent)</li><li>Responsible behavior (29 percent)</li><li>Flexible returns and refunds (25 percent)</li></ol>



<p>So how can you possibly understand what your customers most want from you?</p>



<p><a href="https://sleeknote.com/blog/customer-satisfaction-surveys" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">E-commerce surveys</a> hold the answer. Here are 15 examples—plus what’s good about each—to help you build your next survey.</p>


<div id="contentupgrade-block_5e9ff85a7a3a4" class="block-content-upgrade">
