<h2 id="1"><strong>1. Charlotte Tilbury</strong></h2>



<p><a href="https://www.charlottetilbury.com/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">Charlotte Tilbury</a> is an upper-tier cosmetics brand with an aspirational product set. This is reflected in its e-commerce surveys, which have a pretty high-end feel to them.</p>



<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large"><img width="401" height="1024" src="https://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image1-9-401x1024.png" alt="" class="wp-image-118459" srcset="https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image1-9-401x1024.png 401w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image1-9-118x300.png 118w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image1-9-602x1536.png 602w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image1-9-380x970.png 380w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image1-9-600x1531.png 600w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image1-9-14x35.png 14w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image1-9-20x50.png 20w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image1-9-192x490.png 192w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image1-9-220x561.png 220w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image1-9-385x982.png 385w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image1-9.png 627w" sizes="(max-width: 401px) 100vw, 401px" /></figure></div>



<p>The tone of voice is spot-on, referring to the shopper as “Darling”, and inviting them to “tag your Tilbury” on social media—you wouldn’t do that with a €10 bottle of foundation you picked up at the supermarket.</p>



<p>But this email isn’t all style and no substance. There are some smart design choices here, too.</p>



<p>By laying out multiple purchases in the same email, rather than requesting reviews on multiple items individually, the whole process is streamlined. That’s effective because the last thing you want is to make it hard for customers to <a href="https://sleeknote.com/blog/customer-testimonials" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">review your products</a>.</p>



<p>This choice of layout also subtly reminds you how many items you bought at once, and therefore how much you love Charlotte Tilbury. Maybe it’s time to buy some more?</p>



<h2 id="2"><strong>2. ASOS</strong></h2>



<p><a href="https://sleeknote.com/blog/fashion-popup-examples" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Fashion</a> e-commerce giant <a href="http://asos.com" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">ASOS</a> saw its <a href="https://www.statista.com/statistics/485103/asos-revenue-worldwide/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">revenues increase sixfold</a> between 2012 and 2020 to almost €4 billion, so it’s clearly doing something right. One of those things is definitely its e-commerce surveys.</p>



<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large"><img width="420" height="1024" src="https://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image6-10-420x1024.png" alt="" class="wp-image-118460" srcset="https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image6-10-420x1024.png 420w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image6-10-123x300.png 123w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image6-10-630x1536.png 630w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image6-10-380x926.png 380w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image6-10-600x1462.png 600w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image6-10-14x35.png 14w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image6-10-21x50.png 21w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image6-10-201x490.png 201w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image6-10-220x536.png 220w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image6-10-385x938.png 385w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image6-10.png 645w" sizes="(max-width: 420px) 100vw, 420px" /></figure></div>



<p>Imagine you’re the customer who just received that email. Your order arrived earlier today and you love everything in it. Maybe you’re even wearing your new oversized vintage shirt right now.</p>



<p>But however much you love a purchase, it’s not always easy to put your thoughts into words. What <em>specifically </em>do you love about it?</p>



<p>This is a problem because a lot of review sites don’t just ask for a star rating—they want to know <em>why </em>you like it, too. That’s understandable because a bunch of blank five-star reviews looks super spammy. But on the other hand, it could be putting people off leaving reviews at all.</p>



<p>ASOS prevents this by giving shoppers a few subtle examples of the sort of feedback they could leave in the first paragraph of the copy.</p>



<h2 id="3"><strong>3. Zippi</strong></h2>



<p><a href="https://www.zippi.co.uk/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">Zippi</a> is a small, UK-based company that allows you to print and frame your photos (among other things). As with lots of smaller brands—and a lot of large ones, too—it leans on <a href="https://www.feefo.com/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">Feefo</a> to power its e-commerce reviews.</p>



<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large"><img width="600" height="914" src="https://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image13-4.png" alt="" class="wp-image-118461" srcset="https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image13-4.png 600w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image13-4-197x300.png 197w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image13-4-380x579.png 380w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image13-4-23x35.png 23w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image13-4-33x50.png 33w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image13-4-322x490.png 322w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image13-4-220x335.png 220w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image13-4-385x586.png 385w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px" /></figure></div>



<p>This email is a useful example of a survey that deals with the most important thing first—in this case, seeking your overall feedback on the experience of shopping with Zippi.</p>



<p>Once you’ve got the big-picture stuff out the way, you can drill down into more specific questions that help you add meaning to the overall verdict.</p>



<h2 id="4"><strong>4. Sports Direct</strong></h2>



<p>Whereas Zippi has partnered with Feefo to generate customer reviews, <a href="https://www.sportsdirect.com/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">Sports Direct</a> has gone with another of the big hitters, <a href="https://www.trustpilot.com/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">Trustpilot</a>.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img width="600" height="689" src="https://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image9-7.png" alt="" class="wp-image-118462" srcset="https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image9-7.png 600w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image9-7-261x300.png 261w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image9-7-380x436.png 380w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image9-7-30x35.png 30w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image9-7-44x50.png 44w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image9-7-427x490.png 427w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image9-7-220x253.png 220w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image9-7-385x442.png 385w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px" /></figure>



<p>What’s so great about this email? It may not look flashy, but that simple star-rating graphic is highly impactful.</p>



<p>Visuals are important. Indeed, 33% of us are visual learners, making it the <a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC4340450/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">most common learning style</a>.</p>



<p>Sports Direct uses this to its advantage, guiding the customer with a visual representation of a “review”. I challenge anyone who receives that email <em>not </em>to click one of the rating boxes.</p>



<h2 id="5"><strong>5. Amazon</strong></h2>



<p><a href="http://amazon.com/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">Amazon’s</a> entire business is built around <a href="https://wwd.com/business-news/technology/bezos-says-customer-delight-heart-of-amazon-success-10866159/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">delighting customers</a>, so it’s no surprise its e-commerce surveys are so effective.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img width="680" height="865" src="https://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image4-10.png" alt="" class="wp-image-118463" srcset="https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image4-10.png 680w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image4-10-236x300.png 236w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image4-10-380x483.png 380w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image4-10-600x763.png 600w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image4-10-28x35.png 28w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image4-10-39x50.png 39w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image4-10-385x490.png 385w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image4-10-220x280.png 220w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /></figure>



<p class="has-text-align-center"><em>Source: </em><a href="https://reallygoodemails.com/emails/smiles-davis-how-do-you-like-your-legendary-whitetails-mens-maverick-slub-henley" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow"><em>ReallyGoodEmails</em></a></p>



<p>For instance, maybe there’s only one issue on which you really want <a href="https://sleeknote.com/blog/customer-feedback" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">feedback</a>. Amazon does this by asking for specific insight on how well this product fits because that’s clearly important to shoppers.</p>



<p>If you’ve got a large customer base, you don’t necessarily need to ask every question to every customer. By asking one customer about sizing, one about delivery, and another about comfort, you increase your chances of getting a response (because your survey is so quick and simple), while also generating highly specific feedback.</p>



<h2 id="6"><strong>6. Everlane</strong></h2>



<p>This email demonstrates how it’s not <em>always </em>the right idea to ask the broadest possible question first up; it depends entirely on the goal of your survey.</p>



<p>Your customers are busy. What’s more, they receive a lot of emails. By 2022, we’ll receive an average of <a href="https://www.radicati.com/wp/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/Email-Statistics-Report-2018-2022-Executive-Summary.pdf" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">333 business and consumer emails a day</a>, or 14 an hour. It’s exhausting just thinking about it.</p>



<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large"><img width="404" height="1024" src="https://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image8-7-404x1024.png" alt="" class="wp-image-118464" srcset="https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image8-7-404x1024.png 404w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image8-7-380x962.png 380w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image8-7-600x1519.png 600w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image8-7-14x35.png 14w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image8-7-20x50.png 20w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image8-7-220x557.png 220w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image8-7-385x975.png 385w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image8-7.png 632w" sizes="(max-width: 404px) 100vw, 404px" /></figure></div>



<p class="has-text-align-center"><em>Source: </em><a href="https://reallygoodemails.com/emails/matthew-share-your-thoughts-and-get-a-chance-at-a-200-gift-card" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow"><em>ReallyGoodEmails</em></a></p>



<p>That’s why it’s a good idea to give customers a little incentive to complete your survey. <a href="https://www.everlane.com/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">Everlane</a> does this by offering shoppers who fill in its survey a chance to win a $200 gift card.</p>



<p>This is a double win. Not only does it make me more likely to give feedback, but it also demonstrates how much Everlane values my opinion and is committed to improving its customer experience.</p>



<h2 id="7"><strong>7. MeUndies</strong></h2>



<p>We love <a href="https://sleeknote.com/blog/meundies-marketing" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">MeUndies</a> so much at Sleeknote, we spent a month analyzing the brand’s whole <a href="https://sleeknote.com/blog/e-commerce-marketing-strategies" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">marketing strategy</a>.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img width="680" height="684" src="https://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image2-10.png" alt="" class="wp-image-118466" srcset="https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image2-10.png 680w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image2-10-298x300.png 298w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image2-10-150x150.png 150w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image2-10-380x382.png 380w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image2-10-600x604.png 600w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image2-10-35x35.png 35w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image2-10-50x50.png 50w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image2-10-487x490.png 487w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image2-10-220x221.png 220w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image2-10-385x387.png 385w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image2-10-120x120.png 120w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /></figure>



<p class="has-text-align-center"><em>Source: </em><a href="https://reallygoodemails.com/emails/help-us-improve-your-membership-experience" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow"><em>ReallyGoodEmails</em></a></p>



<p>In this example, MeUndies demonstrates that not all e-commerce surveys have to be specifically linked to a recent purchase. Instead, this email asks for feedback on the company’s <a href="https://sleeknote.com/blog/customer-loyalty-programs" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">membership program</a>.</p>



<p>The lesson here? Don’t be afraid to reach out to customers who haven’t bought from you in a while, provided you’ve got something worthwhile to ask.</p>



<h2 id="8"><strong>8. Target</strong></h2>



<p>Low review scores are a nightmare for e-commerce brands. According to Inc contributor and entrepreneur Andrew Thomas, it takes roughly <a href="https://www.inc.com/andrew-thomas/the-hidden-ratio-that-could-make-or-break-your-company.html" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">40 positive customer experiences</a> to outweigh the impact of a single negative review.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img width="614" height="1024" src="https://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image5-10-614x1024.png" alt="" class="wp-image-118467" srcset="https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image5-10-614x1024.png 614w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image5-10-180x300.png 180w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image5-10-380x634.png 380w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image5-10-600x1001.png 600w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image5-10-21x35.png 21w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image5-10-30x50.png 30w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image5-10-294x490.png 294w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image5-10-220x367.png 220w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image5-10-385x642.png 385w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image5-10.png 680w" sizes="(max-width: 614px) 100vw, 614px" /></figure>



<p class="has-text-align-center"><em>Source: </em><a href="https://reallygoodemails.com/emails/what-did-you-think-of-your-recent-order-65006006500600" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow"><em>ReallyGoodEmails</em></a></p>



<p><a href="https://www.target.com/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">Target</a> recognizes this—so it urges shoppers to fix any issues <em>before </em>they submit their review.</p>



<p>Sure, you might think Target is “cooking the books” on its review scores here. But there’s nothing wrong with asking customers to give you a chance to fix something before they leave a damaging one-star review.</p>



<h2 id="9"><strong>9. Hers</strong></h2>



<p>This one isn’t technically a survey at all. Instead, it’s an infographic embedded in an email, detailing the results of an earlier survey.</p>



<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large"><img width="315" height="1024" src="https://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image7-7-315x1024.png" alt="" class="wp-image-118468" srcset="https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image7-7-315x1024.png 315w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image7-7-92x300.png 92w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image7-7-472x1536.png 472w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image7-7-380x1236.png 380w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image7-7-11x35.png 11w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image7-7-15x50.png 15w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image7-7-151x490.png 151w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image7-7-220x715.png 220w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image7-7-385x1252.png 385w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image7-7.png 492w" sizes="(max-width: 315px) 100vw, 315px" /></figure></div>



<p class="has-text-align-center"><em>Source: </em><a href="https://reallygoodemails.com/emails/heres-the-goop" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow"><em>ReallyGoodEmails</em></a></p>



<p>So why have I included it? Because you should definitely learn from (and steal) this tactic.</p>



<p>Not only does it make for an engaging piece of content in its own right, but it also demonstrates how much you care about improving customer experience. Plus it’s an opportunity to sell something—look at all the products referenced in the results.</p>



<h2 id="10"><strong>10. Drop</strong></h2>



<p>As I’ve already pointed out, we all receive <em>a lot </em>of emails. So it can feel like a real relief opening one that doesn’t bombard you with huge, bright text, emojis, GIFs, and dozens of hyperlinks.</p>



<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large"><img width="544" height="1024" src="https://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image15-3-544x1024.png" alt="" class="wp-image-118469" srcset="https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image15-3-544x1024.png 544w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image15-3-159x300.png 159w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image15-3-380x715.png 380w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image15-3-600x1129.png 600w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image15-3-19x35.png 19w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image15-3-27x50.png 27w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image15-3-260x490.png 260w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image15-3-220x414.png 220w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image15-3-385x725.png 385w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image15-3.png 680w" sizes="(max-width: 544px) 100vw, 544px" /></figure></div>



<p class="has-text-align-center"><em>Source: </em><a href="https://reallygoodemails.com/emails/how-do-you-like-the-massdrop-x-tokyo-keyboard-tokyo60-keyboard-kit" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow"><em>ReallyGoodEmails</em></a></p>



<p><a href="https://drop.com/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Drop</a> takes a clean, uncluttered approach to its e-commerce survey emails. There’s nothing to distract the reader here—just a link to the product, a <a href="https://sleeknote.com/blog/call-to-action" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">call to action</a> at the top of the email, an image, and the visual cue of a star rating system.</p>



<p>On another note, linking to the product—as Drop does here—can be super effective, too. It helps your customer find it quickly and remind themselves of things like pricing and specifications that they might want to reference in their review.</p>



<h2 id="11"><strong>11. Bellroy</strong></h2>



<p>Obviously, the main reason to send an e-commerce survey is to acquire the data you need to improve your customer experience. But that doesn’t mean you can’t <em>also</em> use it to lay the groundwork for <a href="https://sleeknote.com/blog/customer-retention-emails" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">retaining customers</a> and encouraging repeat purchases.</p>



<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large"><img width="485" height="1024" src="https://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image12-4-485x1024.png" alt="" class="wp-image-118470" srcset="https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image12-4-485x1024.png 485w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image12-4-142x300.png 142w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image12-4-380x802.png 380w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image12-4-600x1267.png 600w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image12-4-17x35.png 17w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image12-4-24x50.png 24w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image12-4-232x490.png 232w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image12-4-220x465.png 220w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image12-4-385x813.png 385w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image12-4.png 618w" sizes="(max-width: 485px) 100vw, 485px" /></figure></div>



<p class="has-text-align-center"><em>Source: </em><a href="https://reallygoodemails.com/emails/day-30-what-s-happened-so-far" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow"><em>ReallyGoodEmails</em></a></p>



<p>That’s exactly what <a href="https://sleeknote.com/blog/bellroy-marketing" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Bellroy</a> does here. By positioning a purchase as the start of a journey, rather than a one-off transaction, this survey email paves the way for building a long-term relationship with the customer.</p>



<p>Additionally, the language puts the reader in a positive frame of mind for their review, using phrases like “slimmed your pockets” and “streamlined your things” to reiterate Bellroy’s key features and benefits.</p>



<p>The use of a five-star line-break below the intro text is another nice touch, guiding the customer toward leaving a positive review.</p>



<h2 id="12"><strong>12. Joyus</strong></h2>



<p>According to <a href="https://blog.hubspot.com/blog/tabid/6307/bid/30239/71-More-Likely-to-Purchase-Based-on-Social-Media-Referrals-Infographic.aspx" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">HubSpot</a>, 75 percent of consumers don’t accept ads as truth. On the flip side, 90 percent trust brand recommendations from friends.</p>



<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large"><img width="680" height="741" src="https://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image14-4.png" alt="" class="wp-image-118472" srcset="https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image14-4.png 680w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image14-4-275x300.png 275w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image14-4-380x414.png 380w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image14-4-600x654.png 600w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image14-4-32x35.png 32w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image14-4-46x50.png 46w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image14-4-450x490.png 450w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image14-4-220x240.png 220w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image14-4-385x420.png 385w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /></figure></div>



<p class="has-text-align-center"><em>Source: </em><a href="https://reallygoodemails.com/emails/we-have-one-question" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow"><em>ReallyGoodEmails</em></a></p>



<p>This demonstrates the value of word-of-mouth marketing—something that <a href="https://www.joyus.com/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">Joyus</a> clearly recognizes, prompting it to ask the classic <a href="https://sleeknote.com/blog/customer-satisfaction-surveys#leverage-an-nps-survey" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">NPS</a> question: “How likely are you to refer us to a friend?”</p>



<p>By repeating this survey over time, Joyus can gauge whether its actions are making customers more or less likely to recommend the brand.</p>



<p>What’s more, by asking this specific question, customers are encouraged to <em>think about </em>recommending Joyus. Again, it’s a double win.</p>



<h2 id="13"><strong>13. Nokia</strong></h2>



<p>When it comes to encouraging survey completions, it pays to set expectations early, as <a href="https://www.nokia.com/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">Nokia</a> does here.</p>



<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large"><img width="680" height="832" src="https://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image11-5.png" alt="" class="wp-image-118474" srcset="https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image11-5.png 680w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image11-5-245x300.png 245w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image11-5-380x465.png 380w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image11-5-600x734.png 600w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image11-5-29x35.png 29w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image11-5-41x50.png 41w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image11-5-400x490.png 400w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image11-5-220x269.png 220w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image11-5-385x471.png 385w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /></figure></div>



<p class="has-text-align-center"><em>Source: </em><a href="https://reallygoodemails.com/emails/hi-smiles-davis-how-are-you-liking-body" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow"><em>ReallyGoodEmails</em></a></p>



<p>Once the customer understands exactly how long it’ll take to fill out your e-commerce survey, they can decide whether they’ve got time for it right now. That makes them more likely to start (and complete) it.</p>



<p>Research suggests the ideal survey length is <a href="https://journals.sagepub.com/doi/abs/10.2501/IJMR-2017-039?journalCode=mrea" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">10 minutes</a>, so Nokia’s two-minute survey certainly shouldn’t put too many people off.</p>



<h2 id="14"><strong>14. Taylor Stitch</strong></h2>



<p>The last thing you want is for someone to click through to your survey, only to bounce back off immediately when they see how many questions you expect them to answer.</p>



<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large"><img width="505" height="1024" src="https://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image10-7-505x1024.png" alt="" class="wp-image-118476" srcset="https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image10-7-505x1024.png 505w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image10-7-148x300.png 148w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image10-7-380x771.png 380w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image10-7-600x1218.png 600w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image10-7-17x35.png 17w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image10-7-25x50.png 25w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image10-7-241x490.png 241w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image10-7-220x446.png 220w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image10-7-385x781.png 385w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image10-7.png 680w" sizes="(max-width: 505px) 100vw, 505px" /></figure></div>



<p class="has-text-align-center"><em>Source: </em><a href="https://reallygoodemails.com/emails/feedback-please-review" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow"><em>ReallyGoodEmails</em></a></p>



<p><a href="https://www.taylorstitch.com/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">Taylor Stitch</a> gets around this by incorporating the entire survey within the body of the email. That means it’s super clear what’s expected of the customer, which should lead to low abandonment rates.</p>



<h2 id="15"><strong>15. Warby Parker</strong></h2>



<p>All of the examples I’ve included up to this point work well for pure-play e-commerce stores. But what if you have both an e-commerce operation and physical, brick-and-mortar stores?</p>



<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large"><img width="680" height="1004" src="https://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image3-9.png" alt="" class="wp-image-118477" srcset="https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image3-9.png 680w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image3-9-203x300.png 203w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image3-9-380x561.png 380w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image3-9-600x886.png 600w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image3-9-24x35.png 24w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image3-9-34x50.png 34w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image3-9-332x490.png 332w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image3-9-220x325.png 220w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image3-9-385x568.png 385w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /></figure></div>



<p class="has-text-align-center"><em>Source: </em><a href="https://reallygoodemails.com/emails/nice-seeing-you" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow"><em>ReallyGoodEmails</em></a></p>



<p><a href="https://www.warbyparker.com/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">Warby Parker</a> is an example of a brand with both a high street and online presence.&nbsp;</p>



<p>With this survey example, it manages to take offline interactions online by capturing an email address in-store and sending a feedback survey. That way, it can make customer experience improvements based on feedback from <em>all </em>shoppers, not just those who buy online.</p>


